    <div class="question">
        <h3>What does main.hbs used for?</h3>
        <p>
           The main.hbs file is a crucial component of our website's templating system. It acts as the main template that sets the foundation for the overall structure and design elements that will be present across all pages of the website.

            In the main.hbs file, we typically define the following components:
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Header:</strong> This component represents the top section of the website and usually contains the website logo, branding elements, and any important navigation links or search functionality.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Navigation Menu:</strong>This component includes the menu or navigation bar that allows users to navigate between different pages or sections of the website. It provides links to various pages, such as the home page, about page, contact page, and other relevant sections.
            </li>

            <li>
                <strong>Footer:</strong>The footer component is located at the bottom of each page and often contains additional navigation links, copyright information, social media icons, and other relevant content.
            </li>

        </ul>
            By using the main.hbs layout as the foundation for all pages, we ensure consistency in terms of the overall look and feel of the website. This approach simplifies the development process and allows for easy maintenance and updates across multiple pages. Any changes made to the main.hbs file will automatically reflect on all pages that utilize it as their layout template.

            Overall, the main.hbs file plays a crucial role in providing a unified and consistent user experience throughout the website by defining the common structural and design elements shared across all pages.
        </p>
    </div>

